    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "A student is creating a chatbot for their school's website to help answer frequently asked questions. They want to practice using string methods like <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">indexOf()</code> and <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">substring()</code> to extract parts of speech from a string.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #1:** Complete the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">getDogPart()</code> method in the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Chatbot</code> class. This method should:\r\n\r\n- Use <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">indexOf()</code> and <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">substring()</code> to extract the part of speech for the word <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">\"dog\"</code> from a string containing entries separated by commas.\r\n- Return the string <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">\"dog: noun\"</code> exactly.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #2:** In the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">ChatbotRunner</code> class, call the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">getDogPart()</code> method and print the result.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\r\n💡 <strong>TIP:</strong> The string uses the format <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">word:part</code>, with commas between each pair. Use <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">indexOf()</code> to find where \"dog\" starts and where the comma after it is.\r\n</div>\r\n",
